![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/e6cc26cd-5812-4595-beb8-fdecbabab679/e353.jpg)

In this episode, we dive into the dark and gripping world of _The Black Mirror_ by Scott Snyder. Join us as we explore one of the most critically acclaimed Batman storylines that takes Gotham's detective work to chilling new depths. From Dick Grayson’s role as the Caped Crusader to the eerie mysteries lurking beneath the city, we dissect the twisted tales that push our heroes to their limits. Tune in as we discuss the intricate storytelling, haunting visuals, and what makes this noir-inspired thriller a must-read for any Batman fan!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

